Body.hs_Para:
Mr
Swire: There are trade attaches in 15 African countries
who work to promote British exports and attract inwards investment to
the UK. These countries are: Algeria; Angola; Egypt; Ethiopia; Ghana;
Kenya; Libya; Morocco; Mozambique; Nigeria; South Africa; Sudan;
Tanzania; Tunisia and Uganda.

